00:45:51.679 --> 00:45:58.279
God, I pray that you'd help each of us this morning to follow you.

00:45:58.279 --> 00:46:09.919
Lord, many that are here this morning that you've called them to a particular profession,

00:46:09.919 --> 00:46:16.880
but greater than that profession, you've called them to follow you in that profession, to

00:46:16.880 --> 00:46:26.279
be a doctor that follows Jesus, to be a nurse that follows Jesus, to be an accountant, a

00:46:26.279 --> 00:46:36.359
lawyer, a military first responder, whatever it is, to follow Jesus.

00:46:36.359 --> 00:46:44.279
Perhaps this morning you've placed a more specific call in someone's heart and life.

00:46:44.279 --> 00:46:48.399
A call such as what you placed upon Matthew's life in this text of Scripture.

00:46:48.399 --> 00:46:55.639
Oh, God, I pray that if that would be the case, that they'd respond in obedience, surrender.

00:46:55.639 --> 00:46:58.359
Lord, help each of us.

00:46:58.359 --> 00:47:02.720
We so often sing the song, I surrender all.

00:47:02.720 --> 00:47:10.199
I hope that as we sing that song, that we sing it in truth.

00:47:10.199 --> 00:47:12.959
There's nothing that we hold on to.

00:47:12.959 --> 00:47:17.760
We would not be willing to give up to follow you.

00:47:17.760 --> 00:47:20.440
Use us, God, for your honor and for your glory.

00:47:20.440 --> 00:47:23.079
Work in the time of invitation as only you can.

00:47:23.079 --> 00:47:24.600
We'll thank you for it.

00:47:24.600 --> 00:47:25.119
Would you stand with me?

